</emphasis>
: Sicily, Palermo, Monte Pellegrino (
<figureCitation box="[714,812,1325,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 107 – 108. 107" captionStartId="33.[151,263,1580,1603]" captionTargetBox="[368,1217,209,1540]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[354,1232,193,1559]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 107 – 108. 107: Palermo, Monte Pellegrino, type locality of Pseudomeira exigua (Stierlin, 1861) and Pseudomeira pfisteri (Stierlin, 1864). 108: Palermo, Madonie mountain, Piano Battaglietta type locality of Pseudomeira petrensis sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204892/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="37">
